Control flow inside a <pre> subtree: the body EDGES are syntax (the parser
trims whitespace immediately inside control-flow braces even under preserve),
so the construct keeps its block layout — but INTERIOR body whitespace is
content and the nodes glue verbatim, with no injected breaks between them.
Interior text lands at column zero on purpose: those bytes render.
-- input.gsx --
package p

component C(lines []string) {
	<pre>{ if len(lines) > 0 {
		<b>{ lines[0] }</b>
	} }</pre>
	<pre>{ if len(lines) > 1 {
		<b>a</b>
mid
<b>b</b>
	} }</pre>
	<pre>{ for _, l := range lines {
		<span>{ l }</span>
	} }</pre>
	<pre>{ switch len(lines) {
		case 0:
			<i>empty</i>
		default:
			<i>a</i>
raw
<i>b</i>
	} }</pre>
	<pre><><span>x</span>
between
<span>y</span></></pre>
}
